On 1/31/03 9:13 AM, "Charles Claassen" <charlesclaassen(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

> Anybody have any experience with the plastic vibration dampeners used to
> prevent case bolts from loosening?  I'm getting ready to do a rebuild...didn't
> see any reference to them in Tom Wilson's book.
> 
> Charles

They should be in your gasket set, and they need to be replaced every time
you split the case. They are in the Wilson book, on page 123, the lower
right illustration.

